import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup as bs

# Open a new browser tab and navigate to the Amazon page for the book you want to buy.
amazon_link = 'https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00VKF9JL8?ie=UTF8&tag=thefrugalblogger-20&linkCode=AS2&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=B00VKF9JL8'

# Use the requests library to make a GET request to the URL above and save the response to a string variable called html_page
response = requests.get(amazon_link)

# Use the BeautifulSoup library to parse the HTML returned by the GET request and get the relevant information we need
soup = bs(response.content, 'html.parser')

# Get the title of the book we want to buy
book_title = soup.select('#bv-card-title')[0].text

# Get the author of the book we want to buy
book_author = soup.select('#bv-card-author')[0].text

# Get the price of the book we want to buy
book_price = soup.select('#bv-price')[0].text

# Get the number of pages in the book we want to buy
book_pages = soup.select('#bv-pages')[0].text

# Get a list of reviews for the book we want to buy
reviews = soup.select('#bv-reviews')

# Loop through each review on this page and get its title and content using selectors in Python
for review in reviews:
    review_title = review.select('div h2').text
    review_content = review.select('p').text

# Write all of these details into a list so you can store them for later use when writing your email to your friend
reviews_details = [book_title, book_author, book_price, book_pages, reviews_title, reviews_content]

# Email your friend about your purchase and include this information in your email
sendmail(reviews_details)
